===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|seyk}}
From {{der|en|la|dēsiccāre||to dry completely, dry up}} {{suffix|en||ate|pos2=''verb suffix indicating acting in the specified manner''}}.<ref>Compare {{R:OED Online|pos=v|id=50817|date=1895|nodot=yes}}; {{R:Oxford Dictionaries Online}}</ref> ''Dēsiccāre'' is derived from {{m|la|dēsiccō||to dessicate, dry up; to drain dry}} (from {{m|la|dē-|pos=''prefix meaning ‘completely, to exhaustion’''}} + {{m|la|siccō||to dry; to drain, exhaust}}, from {{m|la|siccus||dry}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*seyk-}}) + {{m|la|-āre}}.

The adjective is derived from {{der|en|la|dēsiccātus||dried up}},<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=adj|id=50816|date=1895}}</ref> the {{glossary|perfect}} {{glossary|passive}} {{glossary|participle}} of {{m|la|dēsiccō}}: ''see above''. The noun is derived from the adjective.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=n|id=50815|date=1972}}</ref>

